short.value: Extension : Object Rendering Settings

definition.value: Extension : Object Rendering Settings

short.value: id : Uniquely identifies the specific redering settings instance. Must be Unique.
label: text used for describing the rendering settings instance
hidden : Kids if the rendering settings are hidden or not Boolean value.
description : Human readable explanation of what the rendering settings are for.
pattern : Describes the specific regular expression pattern used within a rendering setting.
unique : Indicates of the value of the setting is to be distinctive
disabled : Indicates if the specific rendering settings is enabled or disabled
type : Indicates the UIUX specific display component to be used example text, checkbox, text area.
value : Contains the value entered by the end user for this specific rendering setting
required : Indicates if the specific rendering setting is or is not required
maxLength : Indicates the maximum length of the rendering setting value
minLength : Indicates minimum length of the rendering setting value
maxValue : Indicates the maximum value that can be held within the rendering settings value
minValue : Indicates the minimum value that can be held within the rendering settings value
version : Indicates the version number of the widget used to display the rendering settings and votes
